      "returns": "The \"int\" representation of the number of seconds in the timeframe string.",
      "example": "//@version=6indicator(\"`timeframe_in_seconds()`\"),// Get a user-selected timeframe.tfInput = input.timeframe(\"1D\")// Convert it into an \"int\" number of seconds.secondsInTf = timeframe.in_seconds(tfInput)plot(secondsInTf)",
      "remarks": "When the timeframe is \"1M\" or more, calculations use 2628003 as the number of seconds in one month, which represents 30.4167 (365/12) days.",
